    Swipe through to catch up on today’s eclipse — plus, here are 3 @googlepixel tips for taking your own sky photography:

    ☀️ To focus your pic, try tapping on edges within the frame, like where the sky meets the sun’s edge. Alternatively, you can adjust the slider in Pro Controls for a totally manual option.

    ☀️ Reduce accidental shakes by using a tripod or controlling your phone with the Google Camera app on your Pixel Watch. Alternatively, you can tap the Photo Settings button on the bottom left side of your phone screen in the Camera app and set a timer for the shutter.

    ☀️ Compose your photo by enabling the grid in the Pixel camera app. Tap the Settings button in the bottom left corner and try placing the eclipse in a spot where the lines intersect.

    Tap the link in our bio to learn more. #TeamPixel #Pixel8 Pro
